{
  "stem": "13471.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If, if you didn't do this-- the old-fashioned way required, let's say for a one-hour speech, then there would have to be a one-hour translation into French, an additional one-hour translation into German, an additional one-hour translation into Russian, making a total of four hours to do one hour's worth of business.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was simply impossibly complicated-- difficult.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was trying to get a shortcut.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That-- that intolerable delay-- use this four-language system.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, that meant that the interpreter had to sit there behind their little screen with earphones on, listening to the speaker in, let's say, German.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then he would hold a microphone in his hand.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he would interpret immediately into English.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, I don't know if you know anything about German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the Germans have a nasty habit of hanging their verbs at the end of a sentence.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, you couldn't wait for that verb for the end of a sentence because, if you did, by the time you got it all out, the speaker would be halfway through the next sentence, all of which you would have missed.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In other words, you had to anticipate what that speaker was going to say when he got to the end of that sentence.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And another thing the Germans do that's very nasty, they put the 'nicht,' the negative, just in front of the verb at the end of the sentence.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So you would-- you would anticipate the, the verb that the speaker is working towards, you get it right, and then he'd get there and he'd put in a 'nicht' [GERMAN] on it, you see.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We, we had one girl that was real clever about that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She would say, you think what I said is right?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just the opposite.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then she's going--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Dostert.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
